<p>Mount Washington's hillside location provides excellent southern exposure for solar installations, though steep terrain can increase installation complexity and costs. The neighborhood's mix of older and renovated homes often presents interesting HVAC challenges, with many residents choosing high-efficiency heat pumps to replace aging furnaces. Oakland, home to the University of Pittsburgh, sees strong demand for energy-efficient solutions, with many property owners investing in solar and modern HVAC systems to reduce operating costs and attract environmentally conscious tenants. North Shore developments near the sports stadiums typically feature newer construction that's well-suited for both rooftop solar and traditional ducted HVAC systems.</p>

